Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @aubergine{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds. Pop them onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden,
~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 1/2 tsp salt for
the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and tear it into small pieces. Pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g},
@sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @dried oregano{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@water{100%ml} for the sauce. Season with salt and pepper, then bring the
tomato sauce to the boil.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat to medium and simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir the cooked pasta and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} through
the sauce.

Transfer half the pasta to an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer the roasted aubergine over
the top, then cover with the remaining pasta. Scatter over the mozzarella and
remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Preheat your #grill{} to high heat.

Once hot, grill the pasta bake until the cheese is golden and bubbling,
~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and
@olive oil{1/2%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the bowl and toss to coat in
the dressing.

Serve your chicken and aubergine parmigiana bake in large #bowls{} with the
rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!